<span id="freeTextContainer11961309719853261939"><b>
  <i>JUST FUCK ME NOW.<br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380222758ra/596253.gif' width='340' height='200' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/> <br/><br/>I need the second book like now now now!!<br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380222758ra/248667.gif' width='200' height='200' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/></i>
</b><br/><br/><b>For publishing houses and authors who leave us hanging on the edge of the cliff waiting for the next book...<br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380402561ra/782529.gif' width='340' height='220' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/> </b><br/><br/>&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;<br/><br/><b>
  <i>Let me first of all start by complimenting the cover of this book, which is absolutely brilliantly amazingly hot.</i>
</b><br/><br/>Since Jack Henry McLachlan met Laurelyn Prescott... He broke every rule of the game he made for her.<br/>Its like he was breaking out of his own shell to reach out to her.<br/><span>[image error]</span><br/><br/>Their chemistry was smokin&apos; </span>
  <span id="freeText11961309719853261939" style="display:none"><b>
  <i>JUST FUCK ME NOW.<br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380222758ra/596253.gif" width="340" height="200" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"> <br><br>I need the second book like now now now!!<br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380222758ra/248667.gif" width="200" height="200" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"></i>
</b><br><br><b>For publishing houses and authors who leave us hanging on the edge of the cliff waiting for the next book...<br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1380402561ra/782529.gif" width="340" height="220" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"> </b><br><br>&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;<br><br><b>
  <i>Let me first of all start by complimenting the cover of this book, which is absolutely brilliantly amazingly hot.</i>
</b><br><br>Since Jack Henry McLachlan met Laurelyn Prescott... He broke every rule of the game he made for her.<br>Its like he was breaking out of his own shell to reach out to her.<br><span>[image error]</span><br><br>Their chemistry was smokin' hot! They oozed sensuality!<br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1380402561i/782531._SX540_.jpg" width="440" height="270" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><blockquote>
  <i>
    <b>“Baby, you’ve fucked my mind without touching my body.”</b>
  </i>
</blockquote><br><br>I loved the Author's writing style, it had such a nice flow in the pace and buildup of this book.<br>The story was brilliant, the speed it was running on was amazing. I so didn't want this book to end!<br>I truly loved this book, It keep you on edge throughout until the end.. waiting for the next shoe to drop, waiting for whats going to happen next!<br><br>The characters in this book are fascinatingly good. I enjoyed them all, can't wait to read more about both their families in the second book. Jake's family seemed pretty amazing.<br><br>The pole dance scene... <i>*swoon!*</i><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1380402561i/782532.jpg" width="200" height="320" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>I read the book knowing there was a cliffy[its not a big one, because the sneekpeak into book 2 calms your nerves down], and now I am going to sulk waiting for the next book which will be god knows when. GAH!!<br><br><blockquote>
  <b>
    <i>“But the heart wants what the heart wants.”</i>
  </b>
</blockquote><br><br>first read - Feb '13<br>second read - Aug '14<br>third read - Feb '15</span>
